<subSubSection id="CE8D14D0FF818532FF26F930FD7DF85C" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8628475BFF818532FF26F930FD88F974" blockId="38.[136,1452,1742,1985]" box="[136,583,1742,1768]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FF26F930FEEBF974" bold="true" box="[136,292,1742,1768]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FEEEF930FE59F974" box="[320,406,1742,1768]" name="Guyana" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FE63F930FD8BF974" box="[461,580,1742,1768]" name="Venezuela" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFF818532FF13F90CFD7DF85C" blockId="38.[136,1452,1742,1985]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FF13F90CFEE9F890" bold="true" box="[189,294,1778,1804]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species has been reported from only 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FD59F90CFC81F890" box="[759,846,1778,1804]" name="Guyana" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FC2DF90CFC35F890" box="[899,1018,1778,1804]" name="Venezuela" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. It is caespitose with slender ramicauls and narrow leaves producing successive single flowers. The habit is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FC52F8E9FB62F8AC" authorityName="Ames &amp; Schweinfurth" authorityYear="1930" box="[1020,1197,1814,1840]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuticaulis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FC52F8E9FB62F8AC" box="[1020,1197,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. hirsuticaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FB4AF8E9FA9FF8AC" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[1252,1360,1815,1840]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FB4AF8E9FA9FF8AC" box="[1252,1360,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. merae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the yellowish to brownish flowers with abaxially shortly pubescent sepals are most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FB3DF8C5FACFF8C8" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[1171,1280,1851,1876]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FB3DF8C5FACFF8C8" box="[1171,1280,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. merae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is only found in 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FF5FF8A0FE81F8E4" box="[241,334,1886,1912]" name="Ecuador" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FE26F8A1FE70F8E5" box="[392,447,1887,1913]" name="Peru" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Peru</collectingCountry>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FD71F8A1FC83F8E4" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[735,844,1887,1912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="merae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FD71F8A1FC83F8E4" box="[735,844,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. merae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the wider petals with a more pronounced narrow, thickened apical section, more pronounced and oblique lateral lobes of the lip and a pair of longitudinal calli emerging below the middle of the lip extending to the base.
</paragraph>
